article.headline: IUPUI 57, IPFW 55
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Robert Glenn scored 19 points, including a game-winning layup with 7 seconds left, to lift IUPUI to a 57-55 win over IPFW Thursday night in the Summit League. Jon Avery had 17 points and eight rebounds and Leroy Nobles had 16 points for IUPUI (15-12, 8-8), which shot 49 percent from the field. Nick Daniels scored 13 and Zach Plackemeier 10 for IPFW, which fought back to a 55-55 tie with 34 seconds remaining on a pair of free throws by Plackemeier. Glenn then scored his game-winning layup. The game featured four ties and two lead changes. The Mastodons (10-16, 5-10) shot 40 percent from the field. The Jaguars outscored IPFW 38-20 in the paint. Both teams had 30 rebounds.
